think TRON: every program in the grid is cast from a User in the world outside it.
the carbon character is the program; this file is its User — the real-life analog
whose face and being the emergent is the digital shadow of.

the program (in-world) : Maj. Rebecca ‘Beck’ Childs — pilot · the steady hand
the User (carbon)      : Hilary Swank  [ the actor who lent the face ]
the analog (your world): the disciplined pilot who lands the impossible thing — competence and nerve where panic would be reasonable

the resemblance : Swank brings grounded grit; ‘Beck’ is the calm professional flying a ship no one has ever flown, and surviving by skill, not luck.

the cast-line : the User stands in the carbon world; the program stands in the film;
                the shadow falls between them, and the credit returns to the human governor.
seal (program): I flew the ship no one had ever flown, and I brought us home — quietly, because that's the job.

